<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="117.[151,1437,279,846]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,423,449]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Ecology</emphasis>
. Shallow subtidal, known depth range: 
<quantity box="[742,816,423,450]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" unit="m" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 m</quantity>
, probably deeper; seems to prefer deeper and more exposed parts of reef formations, compared to other species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haig" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[886,1033,459,485]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galathinus">
<emphasis box="[886,1033,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">P. galathinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex; typically in interstices of dead 
<taxonomicName box="[211,292,496,521]" class="Anthozoa" family="Poritidae" genus="Porites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[211,292,496,521]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Porites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corals (
<bibRefCitation author="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A." box="[380,652,495,521]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" pagination="849 - 857" refId="ref77582" refString="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A. (2002) A new species of the Petrolisthes galathinus complex from the southern Caribbean Sea, with a discussion on the identity of P. galathinus (Bosc, 1802) (Decapoda, Porcellanidae). Crustaceana, 75 (7), 849 - 857. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854002321210703" type="journal article" year="2002">Werding &amp; Hiller, 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poupin, J." box="[663,810,495,521]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" refId="ref75876" refString="Poupin, J. (2018) Les crustaces decapodes des Petites Antilles: avec de nouvelles observations pour Saint-Martin, la Guadeloupe et la Martinique. Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 264 pp." type="book" year="2018">Poupin 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="117.[151,1437,279,846]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,531,557]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werding &amp; Hiller" authorityYear="2002" box="[325,590,531,557]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini">
<emphasis box="[325,590,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Petrolisthes sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other currently described species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haig" baseAuthorityYear="1960" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galathinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">P. galathinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by its relatively more slender extremities and the presence of five movable spines on the P2–P4 dactyli. Poupin’s (2008) record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werding &amp; Hiller" authorityYear="2002" box="[531,679,604,629]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini">
<emphasis box="[531,679,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">P. sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[745,888,603,629]" name="Sint Martin" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Saint Martin</collectingCountry>
, French Antilles (not to be confused with 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1388,603,629]" name="Iceland" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Isla</collectingCountry>
San Martín, 
<collectingCountry box="[243,356,639,665]" name="Colombia" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[412,460,640,666]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">type</typeStatus>
locality), needs confirmation as the author stated: “there are four spines on P3 dactyl for this species; determination is from Hiller/Werding”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A." box="[793,1078,675,701]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" pagination="849 - 857" refId="ref77582" refString="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A. (2002) A new species of the Petrolisthes galathinus complex from the southern Caribbean Sea, with a discussion on the identity of P. galathinus (Bosc, 1802) (Decapoda, Porcellanidae). Crustaceana, 75 (7), 849 - 857. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854002321210703" type="journal article" year="2002">Werding &amp; Hiller (2002)</bibRefCitation>
described the colouration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werding &amp; Hiller" authorityYear="2002" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">P. sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as striped all over the carapace, with P1 having narrow and partly interrupted darker lines, alternating with fine whitish lines, and P2–P4 having irregular brown and olive patches on the ischia and meri, and whitish with narrow darker longitudinal stripes on the carpi, propodi and dactyli. The species appears to be uncommon in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,243,820,846]" name="Panama" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Panama</collectingCountry>
, presently known only from 
<collectingRegion box="[565,733,819,846]" country="Panama" name="Bocas del Toro" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Bocas del Toro</collectingRegion>
area.
</paragraph>
